CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 7, 1945, reads: "AFTER SERVICE - in vicinity of all churches was a riot of color last Sunday, as thousands turned out for Easter services. Little Louise Kemp didn't mind bringing along her Easter bunny, as she and Miss Catherine Bernice Harris join in the Easter Parade wearing "something new," signifying the resurrection." - Harris Photo
TitMainTitle: Catherine Bernice Harris, and Louise Kemp holding easter bunny in front of her face, standing on sidewalk near Centre Avenue YMCA, after Easter services
